[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/comments/1178876067","html_url":"https://github.com/doccano/doccano/issues/1878#issuecomment-1178876067","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1878","id":1178876067,"node_id":"IC_kwDOB-j9wM5GRDij","user":{"login":"Stifo","id":4548538,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1NDg1Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4548538?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo","html_url":"https://github.com/Stifo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-07-08T11:25:43Z","updated_at":"2022-07-08T12:53:14Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Hello, I was trying to achieve the same using [Docker compose](https://github.com/doccano/doccano#docker-compose) with my nginx webserver and got it work by doing following:\r\n\r\n## Doccano\r\n1. in [frontend/nuxt.config.js](https://github.com/doccano/doccano/blob/master/frontend/nuxt.config.js), set [`base`](https://nuxtjs.org/docs/configuration-glossary/configuration-router/#base) to your subpath \r\n\r\n```\r\n...\r\nexport default {\r\n  router: {\r\n    base: '/mysubpath/'\r\n  },\r\n...\r\n```\r\nand set `baseUrl` from `/v1` to `/mysubpath/v1`:\r\n```\r\n...\r\n   env: {\r\n    baseUrl: '/mysubpath/v1'\r\n   },\r\n...\r\n```\r\n2. rebuild the image and run:\r\n```\r\ndocker-compose -f docker/docker-compose.prod.yml up --build\r\n```\r\n3. Configure `conf.d/default.conf` of my nginx webserver, **not the one that comes with doccano's docker-compose.prod.yml**:\r\n```\r\n    location /mysubpath/ {\r\n        proxy_pass          http://doccano-nginx:8080/;\r\n        proxy_set_header    Host $host;\r\n        proxy_set_header    X-Real-IP         $remote_addr;\r\n        proxy_set_header    X-Forwarded-For   $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\r\n        proxy_set_header    X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nwhere `doccano-nginx` is the name of the nginx container in [docker/docker-compose.prod.yml](https://github.com/doccano/doccano/blob/3cd4fd0a655b6414efcbf51914a2954dedb742f4/docker/docker-compose.prod.yml#L58)\r\n\r\n## Django's admin area:\r\n\r\n1. change `STATIC_URL` from `/static/` to `/mysubpath/static/` in [`backend/config/settings/base.py`](https://github.com/doccano/doccano/blob/3cd4fd0a655b6414efcbf51914a2954dedb742f4/backend/config/settings/base.py#L106):\r\n```\r\n...\r\nSTATIC_URL = \"/mysubpath/static/\"\r\n...\r\n```\r\n2. add following settings to [`backend/config/settings/production.py`](https://github.com/doccano/doccano/blob/3cd4fd0a655b6414efcbf51914a2954dedb742f4/backend/config/settings/production.py):\r\n```\r\nUSE_X_FORWARDED_HOST = True\r\nFORCE_SCRIPT_NAME = '/mysubpath/'\r\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/comments/1178876067/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Stifo","id":4548538,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1NDg1Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4548538?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo","html_url":"https://github.com/Stifo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Stifo/gists{/